Introduction

The bugphyzz package provides access to an electronic resource of harmonized microbial annotations from different sources. The resource can also be accessed by direct download at >>> insert Zenodo link here <<<.

Import bugphyzz 

if (!require("BiocManager", quietly = TRUE))
    install.packages("BiocManager")

## Devel version
BiocManager::install("waldronlab/bugphyzz")
library(bugphyzz)
library(dplyr)
library(purrr)

Create signatures

Create signatures of taxids at the genus level for aerophilicity 

aer_sigs_g <- makeSignatures(
  dat = bp[["aerophilicity"]], tax_id_type = "NCBI_ID", tax_level = "genus"
)
map(aer_sigs_g, head)
#> $`bugphyzz:aerophilicity|aerobic`
#> [1] 1330547 1822002 1903434  447792 1649298  413496
#> 
#> $`bugphyzz:aerophilicity|anaerobic`

#> $`bugphyzz:aerophilicity|facultatively anaerobic`
#> [1]    1016 1036132 1069494 1078829  111142  111500

Create signatures of taxa names at the species level for growth temperature 

gt_sigs_sp <- makeSignatures(
  dat = bp[["growth temperature"]], tax_id_type = "Taxon_name",
  tax_level = 'species'
)
map(gt_sigs_sp, head)

Create signatures with custom threshold for numeric attributes 

gt_sigs_mix <- makeSignatures(
  dat = bp[["growth temperature"]], tax_id_type = "Taxon_name",
  tax_level = "mixed", min = 0, max = 25
)
map(gt_sigs_mix, head)
#> $`bugphyzz:growth temperature| >=0 & <=25`
#> [1] "Cryobacterium roopkundense"    "Hugenholtzia roseola"         
#> [3] "Halopseudomonas formosensis"   "Occallatibacter savannae"     
#> [5] "Pectinatus sottacetonis"       "Methylobacterium thuringiense"

Create signatures for a binary attribute 

ap_sigs_mix <- makeSignatures(
  dat = bp[["animal pathogen"]], tax_id_type = "NCBI_ID",
  tax_level = "mixed", evidence = c("exp", "igc", "nas", "tas")
)
map(ap_sigs_mix, head)
#> $`bugphyzz:animal pathogen|FALSE`
